    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 1.6: SENSOR OPERATION - TYPES OF SENSORS -
        MAGNETIC PICKUP
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="f1900609" svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAGNETIC PICKUP</title>
        <para>A magnetic pickup is a sensor used to generate a alternating frequency that indicates speed. Magnetic
            pickups normally have a two wire connection for signal and ground. This sensor is constructed with a
            permanent magnetic core surrounded by a wire coil. The signal frequency is generated by the rotation of gear
            teeth which disturbs the magnetic field created by the magnet.
            <emph type="bold">Refer to Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1900610">1.27</hotlnk>.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <para>Example:</para>
        <para>VSS Vehicle Speed Sensor</para>
        <figure id="f1900610" figsize="col-wide">
